      "id": "PopularPost143519",
      "post_content": "I don't like the ability much at all. The classic use of it would be as response to removal, but its not all the time you get hit with [Dead Ringers](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Dead Ringers) or [Reckless Spite](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Reckless Spite) when cards like [Damnation](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Damnation) and [Overwhelming forces](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Overwhelming forces) and [day of judgement](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=day of judgement) exist. Shroud doesn't help with any of those.   \nA creature that supplies an activated ability that protects against Wrath effects would not be too powerful. It would play the metagame clock in a cool way but not in a way to make it overpowered.  \nMaybe a creature with \"cost: Exile me, and return me at the beginning of your next end step. If you do, [Second Sunrise](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Second Sunrise) at the beginning of your next end step.\"",
      "posted_by": "Kryptnyt",
