    {
      "id": "PopularPost96356",
      "post_content": "I don't think this card is really all that great. I'd rather pay less to give one or two of my creatures shroud with something like sylvan safekeeper or vines of vastwood because my opponent will most likely only be targeting one or two creatures per turn.\n  \n   \n@ Thisprofilemocksyou,\n  \nI don't think you understand what shroud does. A creature with shroud **will** be destroyed by effects that \"destroy all creatures\" because those effects don't target specific creatures. So wrath of god, day of judgment, damnation and nevinyrral's disk will still destroy your creatures even if you've given them shroud. MtG rules are conveniently literal so unless a card specifically says \"target\" in reference to the permanent(s) it intends to effect, shroud is meaningless.",
      "posted_by": "heenaheena",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost96356\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_post\">I don't think this card is really all that great. I'd rather pay less to give one or two of my creatures shroud with something like sylvan safekeeper or vines of vastwood because my opponent will most likely only be targeting one or two creatures per turn.\r<br/> <br/>@ Thisprofilemocksyou,\r<br/>I don't think you understand what shroud does. A creature with shroud <b>will</b> be destroyed by effects that \"destroy all creatures\" because those effects don't target specific creatures. So wrath of god, day of judgment, damnation and nevinyrral's disk will still destroy your creatures even if you've given them shroud. MtG rules are conveniently literal so unless a card specifically says \"target\" in reference to the permanent(s) it intends to effect, shroud is meaningless.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '96356'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy23874\">heenaheena</span>\r\n                                (17/08/2010 23:25:16)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"flo